## Table of Contents

### Classes

#### Public Classes

* [`jamf`](#jamf): This module will handle configuration of Jamf servers both cloud and on-prem

#### Private Classes

* `jamf::firewall`: Opens firewall ports for jamf
* `jamf::install`: Installs jamf using jamf pro installer
* `jamf::mysql`: Installs and configures mysql on target host
* `jamf::on_prem`: Manages the jamf service for on premises jamf servers
* `jamf::tomcat`: Manages tomcat service

This module will handle configuration of Jamf servers both cloud and on-prem

* [`repo_gpgkey`](#-jamf--repo_gpgkey)

##### <a name="-jamf--owner"></a>`owner`

Data type: `String`

The filesystem owner for the directory where the Jamf Pro installer
will live and the installer itself.

@note Used only for on-prem servers.

Default value: `'jamf'`

##### <a name="-jamf--group"></a>`group`

Data type: `String`

The filesystem group for the directory where the Jamf Pro installer
will live and the installer itself.

@note Used only for on-prem servers.

Default value: `'0'`

##### <a name="-jamf--db"></a>`db`

Data type: `Optional[Hash]`

The name to use for the Jamf database which will be created.

@note Used only for on-prem servers.

Default value: `undef`

##### <a name="-jamf--install_dir"></a>`install_dir`

Data type: `String`

The directory in which the Jamf Pro installer will be cached.

@note Used only for on-prem servers

Default value: `'/opt/jamf'`

##### <a name="-jamf--installer_name"></a>`installer_name`

Data type: `String`

param description goes here.

@note Used only for on-prem servers

Default value: `undef`

##### <a name="-jamf--installer_path"></a>`installer_path`

Data type: `String`

param description goes here.

@note Used only for on-prem servers

Default value: `undef`

##### <a name="-jamf--java_opts"></a>`java_opts`

Data type: `Optional[String]`

The Java options which will be passed to Tomcat for each launch

@note Used only for on-prem servers

Default value: `undef`

##### <a name="-jamf--max_backup_age"></a>`max_backup_age`

Data type: `String`

The maximum age of files/folders which will be stored in
/usr/local/jss/backups/.

@note Used only for on-prem servers. Backups are created automatically
during Jamf Pro upgrades and aren't cleaned up automatically.
Long-standing servers can generate quite a bit of cruft here.

Default value: `'+30'`

##### <a name="-jamf--organization"></a>`organization`

Data type: `Optional[String]`

The organization to which this Jamf server belongs.

@note Used as the identifying factor for many providers that don't have
a specific NAME parameter to key off of e.g. SMTP, Inventory Collection, etc.

Default value: `undef`

##### <a name="-jamf--activation_code"></a>`activation_code`

Data type: `Optional[String]`

The activation code for the Jamf server gathered from
account.jamf.com.

Default value: `undef`

##### <a name="-jamf--username"></a>`username`

Data type: `Optional[String]`

The initial admin user which will be used during Setup Assistant
to initialize the Jamf Pro server and also for all additional API
calls made

Default value: `undef`

##### <a name="-jamf--password"></a>`password`

Data type: `Optional[String]`

The password for the initial admin user's account which will be used
for all API calls.

Default value: `undef`

##### <a name="-jamf--is_cloud"></a>`is_cloud`

Data type: `Boolean`

param description

Default value: `false`

##### <a name="-jamf--mysql_overrides"></a>`mysql_overrides`

Data type: `Optional[Hash]`

param description

@note Used only for on-prem servers

Default value: `undef`

##### <a name="-jamf--mysql_root_pass"></a>`mysql_root_pass`

Data type: `Optional[String]`

param description

@note Used only for on-prem servers

Default value: `undef`

##### <a name="-jamf--mysql_version"></a>`mysql_version`

Data type: `Optional[String]`

param description

@note Used only for on-prem servers

Default value: `undef`

##### <a name="-jamf--os_arch"></a>`os_arch`

Data type: `String`

param description

@note Used only for on-prem servers

Default value: `$facts['os']['architecture']`

##### <a name="-jamf--os_version"></a>`os_version`

Data type: `String`

param description

@note Used only for on-prem servers

## Resource types

### <a name="jamf_account"></a>`jamf_account`

Manages a JAMF cloud server's accounts

#### Properties

The following properties are available in the `jamf_account` type.

##### `access_level`

Level of access to grant the account.

##### `casper_admin_privileges`

An array of Casper Admin Privileges for the account.

Default value: `[]`

##### `email`

Email address for the account (e.g. 'john@mycompany.com').

##### `email_address`

Email address for the account (e.g. 'john@mycompany.com').

##### `enabled`

Access status of the account ('Enabled' or 'Disabled').

##### `ensure`

Valid values: `present`, `absent`

The basic property that the resource should be in.

Default value: `present`

##### `force_password_change`

Force user to change password at next login.

Default value: `false`

##### `full_name`

Name of the account holder (e.g. 'John Smith').

##### `jss_actions_privileges`

An array of JSS Actions Privileges for the account.

Default value: `[]`

##### `jss_object_privileges`

An array of JSS Object Privileges for the account.

##### `jss_settings_privileges`

An array of JSS Settings Privileges for the account.

Default value: `[]`

##### `password`

Password for Jamf Pro server user account.

##### `privilege_set`

Set of privileges to grant the account.

#### Parameters

The following parameters are available in the `jamf_account` type.

* [`account_name`](#-jamf_account--account_name)
* [`api_password`](#-jamf_account--api_password)
* [`api_url`](#-jamf_account--api_url)
* [`api_username`](#-jamf_account--api_username)
* [`auth_token`](#-jamf_account--auth_token)
* [`conn_validator`](#-jamf_account--conn_validator)
* [`is_cloud`](#-jamf_account--is_cloud)
* [`jamf_cookie`](#-jamf_account--jamf_cookie)
* [`name`](#-jamf_account--name)
* [`provider`](#-jamf_account--provider)

##### <a name="-jamf_account--account_name"></a>`account_name`

Name of the account for cloud servers.

Default value: `''`

##### <a name="-jamf_account--api_password"></a>`api_password`

Password for authentication to the API.

##### <a name="-jamf_account--api_url"></a>`api_url`

URL of the JAMF API. Note: we will append '/JSSResource/accounts' to the end of this. Default: https://127.0.0.1:8443

Default value: `https://127.0.0.1:8443`

##### <a name="-jamf_account--api_username"></a>`api_username`

Username for authentication to the API.

##### <a name="-jamf_account--auth_token"></a>`auth_token`

Token used for authentication to the API.

Default value: `''`

##### <a name="-jamf_account--conn_validator"></a>`conn_validator`

Title of the jamf_conn_validator resource to auto-require

Default value: `jamf`

##### <a name="-jamf_account--is_cloud"></a>`is_cloud`

Check is server is cloud or internal

Default value: `false`

##### <a name="-jamf_account--jamf_cookie"></a>`jamf_cookie`

Cookie used to avoid cluster refresh issues with cloud servers.

Default value: `''`

##### <a name="-jamf_account--name"></a>`name`

namevar

Name of the account for internal servers.

##### <a name="-jamf_account--provider"></a>`provider`

The specific backend to use for this `jamf_account` resource. You will seldom need to specify this --- Puppet will
usually discover the appropriate provider for your platform.

### <a name="jamf_computer_checkin"></a>`jamf_computer_checkin`

Manages a JAMF server's computer checkin settings

#### Properties

The following properties are available in the `jamf_computer_checkin` type.

##### `apply_computer_level_managed_preferences`

Allow computer-level enforced Managed Preferences to be applied. This may interfere with Managed Preferences from a third-party provider.

Default value: `true`

##### `apply_user_level_managed_preferences`

Allow user-level and user-level enforced Managed Preferences to be applied. This may interfere with Managed Preferences from a third-party provider.

Default value: `true`

##### `check_for_policies_at_login_logout`

Ensure that computers check for policies triggered by login or logout.

Default value: `true`

##### `check_for_policies_at_startup`

Ensure that computers check for policies triggered by startup.

Default value: `true`

##### `check_in_frequency`

Frequency at which computers check in with Jamf Pro for available policies.

Default value: `15`

##### `create_login_logout_hooks`

Create hooks that execute each time a user logs in or logs out. This may disable existing login/logout hooks.

Default value: `true`

##### `create_startup_script`

Create a launch daemon that executes on computers at startup.

Default value: `true`

##### `display_status_to_user`

Display the status of login/logout hook actions. Does not apply to login hook actions performed in the background.

Default value: `true`

##### `ensure`

Valid values: `present`, `absent`

The basic property that the resource should be in.

Default value: `present`

##### `ensure_ssh_is_enabled`

Enable SSH (Remote Login) on computers that have it disabled.

Default value: `true`

##### `hide_restore_partition`

Ensure that the Restore partition is hidden at login.

Default value: `true`

##### `log_startup_event`

Log the date/time of startup.

Default value: `true`

##### `log_username`

Log the username and date/time at login and logout.

Default value: `true`

##### `perform_login_actions_in_background`

Ensure that login hook actions take place in the background to avoid delays during login. Does not apply to Managed Preferences.

Default value: `true`

### <a name="jamf_distribution_point"></a>`jamf_distribution_point`

Manages a JAMF server's file share distribution points

#### Properties

The following properties are available in the `jamf_distribution_point` type.

##### `connection_type`

Protocol of the file server.

##### `ensure`

Valid values: `present`, `absent`

The basic property that the resource should be in.

Default value: `present`

##### `http_context`

Path to the share (e.g. if the share is accessible at http://192.168.10.10/JamfShare, the context is 'JamfShare').

##### `http_downloads_enabled`

Whether or not to allow downloads over HTTP. HTTP downloads must be enabled on the server for this to work.

Default value: `false`

##### `http_port`

Port number of the file server.

Default value: `80`

##### `http_protocol`

HTTP Protocol of the file server.

Default value: `http`

##### `http_username`

Username of account that has read access to the share.

##### `ip_address`

Hostname or IP address of the distribution point server.

##### `is_master`

Whether or not to use as the authoritative source for all files.

Default value: `false`

##### `no_authentication_required`

Whether or not authentication is required to download files from the distribution point.

Default value: `true`

##### `read_only_username`

Username of account that has read-only access to the share.

##### `read_write_username`

Username of account that has read/write access to the share.

##### `share_name`

Name of the share.

##### `share_port`

Port number of the file server.

##### `username_password_required`

Whether or not authentication is required to download files from the distribution point.

Default value: `false`

##### `workgroup_or_domain`

Workgroup or domain of the accounts that have read/write and read-only access to the share.

Valid values: `present`, `absent`

Default value: `636`

Default value: `false`

##### `use_wildcards`

Should LDAP use wildcards for searching or not.

Default value: `true`

Hash of user-group membership mappings, see https://github.com/jamf/Classic-API-Swagger-Specification/blob/master/swagger.yaml

##### `user_mappings`

##### `allow_deferral_until_utc`

Date/time at which deferrals are prohibited and the policy runs

Default value: `''`

##### `allow_users_to_defer`

Default value: `false`

##### `category`

Category to add the policy to

##### `delete_file`

Whether to delete file if found

Default value: `false`

##### `enabled`

Whether this policy is active or not

Default value: `false`

##### `ensure`

##### `excluded_buildings`

##### `excluded_ibeacons`

Default value: `[]`

##### `excluded_network_segments`

Default value: `[]`

##### `excluded_user_groups`

Default value: `[]`

##### `excluded_users`

Users for which to not assign the profile

Default value: `[]`

Date/time to make the policy expire

Default value: `''`

##### `feature_on_main_page`

Default value: `false`

##### `file_vault_2_reboot`

Whether to restart FileVault 2-encrypted computers without requiring an unlock during the next startup

Default value: `false`

##### `fix_byhost`

Whether to fix ByHost Files

Default value: `false`

##### `fix_permissions`

Whether to fix Disk Permissions (Not compatible with macOS v10.12 or later)

Default value: `false`

##### `flush_system_cache`

Whether to flush caches from /Library/Caches/ and /System/Library/Caches/, except for any com.apple.LaunchServices caches

Default value: `false`

##### `flush_user_cache`

Whether to flush caches from ~/Library/Caches/, ~/.jpi_cache/, and ~/Library/Preferences/Microsoft/Office version #/Office Font Cache.
Note: Enabling this may cause problems with system fonts displaying unless a logout trigger or restart option is configured.

Default value: `false`

##### `force_users_to_view_description`

Force users to view the description before the policy runs

Default value: `false`

##### `frequency`

How often the policy should run

##### `install_all_cached_packages`

Whether to install all packages cached by Jamf Pro

Default value: `false`

##### `install_button_text`

Name for the button that users click to initiate the policy

Default value: `Install`

##### `kill_process`

Whether to kill process if found - This works with exact matches only

Default value: `false`

##### `limited_ibeacons`

iBeacons to limit the scope of the policy to

Default value: `[]`

##### `limited_network_segments`

Network Segments to limit the scope of the policy to

Default value: `[]`

Default value: `false`

##### `update_locate_database`

Whether to update the 'locate' database before searching for the file

Default value: `false`

##### `user_logged_in_action`

Reboot action to take if a user is logged in to the computer

Default value: `Do not restart`

##### `verify_startup_disk`

Whether to verify the startup disk

Default value: `false`

### <a name="jamf_reenrollment"></a>`jamf_reenrollment`

Manages a JAMF server's re-enrollment settings

#### Properties

The following properties are available in the `jamf_reenrollment` type.

##### `ensure`

Valid values: `present`, `absent`

The basic property that the resource should be in.

Default value: `present`

##### `flush_extension_attributes`

Clears all values for extension attributes from computer and mobile device inventory information
during re-enrollment. This does not apply to extension attributes populated by scripts or LDAP Attribute Mapping

Default value: `true`

##### `flush_location_information`

Clears computer and mobile device information from the User and Location category on the Inventory tab in inventory information during re-enrollment

Default value: `true`

##### `flush_location_information_history`

Clears computer and mobile device information from the User and Location History category on the History tab in inventory information during re-enrollment

Default value: `true`

##### `flush_mdm_queue`

Clears computer and mobile device information from the Management History category on the History tab in inventory information during re-enrollment

Default value: `DELETE_EVERYTHING`

##### `flush_policy_logs`

Clears the logs for policies that ran on the computer and clears computer information from the Policy Logs category on the History tab in inventory information during re-enrollment

Default value: `true`

### <a name="jamf_restricted_software"></a>`jamf_restricted_software`

Default value: `[]`

##### `kill_process`

Default value: `true`

##### `scoped_departments`

Default value: `[]`

Default value: `false`

### <a name="jamf_smtp_server"></a>`jamf_smtp_server`

Manages the SMTP server used to send email alerts in a Jamf Pro server

#### Properties

The following properties are available in the `jamf_smtp_server` type.

##### `authorization_required`

Does the SMTP server require authentication using credentials for an SMTP account

Default value: `false`

##### `enabled`

Whether to integrate with an SMTP server to use for email communications

Default value: `false`

##### `encryption`

Protocol to use for data encryption. 0 is no encryption, 1 is SSL, 2 is TLSv1.2, 3 is TLSv1.1, 4 is TLSv1

##### `ensure`

Valid values: `present`, `absent`

The basic property that the resource should be in.

Default value: `present`

##### `host`

Hostname or IP address of the SMTP server

##### `port`

Port number of the SMTP server

##### `send_from_email`

SMTP account email address that Jamf Pro will send emails from

##### `send_from_name`

Sender name to display in email messages sent from Jamf Pro

##### `ssl`

Whether SSL will be used to connect to the SMTP server

##### `timeout`

Amount of time in seconds to wait before canceling an attempt to connect to the SMTP server

Default value: `10`

##### `tls`

Whether TLS will be used to connect to the SMTP server

##### `username`

The username for authentication to the SMTP server
